  "title": "Build PirateDev Landing Page",
  "prompt": "Build a complete landing page for PirateDev™, a cloud IDE product. Replace the contents of index.html with a full production landing page.\n\nBRAND: Dark theme. Background #0a0a0a, text #e0e0e0, white accents. Fonts: Inter for body, JetBrains Mono for code/tech elements. The logo is a skull with </> code bracket crossbones. Tone is confident, irreverent, developer-focused. No corporate fluff.\n\nUSE TAILWIND CDN: Add <script src=\"https://cdn.tailwindcss.com\"></script> in the head AND include the tailwind config inline so custom colors work. Keep the Google Fonts links already there.\n\nSECTIONS (single page, smooth scroll):\n\n1. NAV - Sticky. Logo text \"PirateDev™\" left, links right: Features, Pricing, Docs, GitHub. \"Get Early Access\" button.\n\n2. HERO - Full viewport height. Large headline: \"Code Like Nobody's Watching. Deploy Like Everyone Is.\" Subhead: \"A cloud IDE that passes AI costs through at zero markup. No platform tax. No vendor lock-in. Just build.\" Two CTAs: \"Get Early Access\" (primary white button) and \"View on GitHub\" (outline button linking to github.com/jstone6198/piratedev).\n\n3. THE PROBLEM - Brief section. Headline: \"Every Cloud IDE Takes a Cut.\" 3-column grid showing the markup problem: Replit charges 10-20x on AI, Codespaces locks you into Azure, Cursor charges $20/mo for models you could access at cost. Keep it factual and punchy.\n\n4. THE SOLUTION - Headline: \"Zero Markup. Zero Apologies.\" Explain the PirateDev model: you bring your own API keys, we pass costs through at $0 markup, you pay only for compute. Show a fake cost comparison table: \"GPT-4o on Cursor: ~$0.15/request → On PirateDev: ~$0.01/request (actual API cost)\".\n\n5. FEATURES - 6-card grid with icons (use unicode/emoji icons). Cards: Code Editor (Monaco-based, dark theme, every language), AI Chat (Claude, GPT, Groq — your keys, your choice), Agent Mode (describe what you want, AI builds it step by step), Live Preview (see changes instantly, hot reload), One-Click Deploy (deploy to your own VPS, not our servers), Built-in Terminal (full shell access, run anything).\n\n6. OPEN SOURCE - Headline: \"Open Core. Open Rebellion.\" Explain AGPL frontend, proprietary backend. \"See exactly what you're running. Fork it. Improve it. Just don't charge for it without a license.\" Link to GitHub.\n\n7. PRICING - 3 tiers. Free (self-host, bring your own infra, community support), Pro $9/mo (hosted IDE, managed VPS, priority support), Team $29/seat/mo (shared workspaces, team secrets, admin controls). Mark all as \"Coming Soon\" with email capture.\n\n8. CTA SECTION - \"Stop Paying the Platform Tax.\" Email signup for early access waitlist.\n\n9. FOOTER - PirateDev™ © 2026 Josh Stone. Links: GitHub, Docs, License, Contact. \"Built with PirateDev™\" tagline.\n\nTECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:\n- Fully responsive (mobile-first)\n- Smooth scroll behavior\n- Subtle animations on scroll (CSS only, no JS libraries)\n- SEO meta tags, Open Graph tags, Twitter card tags\n- Schema.org JSON-LD for SoftwareApplication\n- All in a single index.html file\n- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively, no custom CSS except animations",
